LLD for a shopping cart system with discounts based on product type, user type and coupon selection

- based on product type - user is eligible for discounts
- cart - collection of multiple products
- different discount types
    - based on product type
    - based on User type
    - user selection coupons ()

- We will have multiple coupon types which will be provided to the user at cart page

Functionality Exposed
1.) Add products to cart along with an associated coupon
2.) System will calculate the discount
3.) System will also provide discount type

There can be different discount strategy which can be applied to the cart.
These discount strategies will have different impact on the aggregation of the discounts.
For example, if we have a discount strategy which is based on product type,
then the discount will be applied to the products in the cart based on their type.
If we have a discount strategy which is based on user type, then the discount will be applied to the entire cart based on the user's type.
If we have a discount strategy which is based on coupon selection,
then the discount will be applied to the entire cart based on the selected coupon.


Entities -
1.) User
2.) User_Type
3.) Product
4.) Product_Type
5.) Coupon
6.) Coupon_Type
7.) Cart
